spanGrp.span: we get the chicken with it [?] and kill it uh…
je wa nã óshkoro guge-gẽ-wã te-gẽ-wã (eh) (_) estee
then we take off all that uh…
tögapanã (_) se të se të kable esteee
we take off its guts and take them out.
je todo ye tule-gẽ-mĩ ĩã se (m) të ñã' bie-gẽ-sã'
Next we cut it into pieces and put it on fire.
kepa tögapa se të í wötie-gẽ-nẽ kemẽ-gẽ-nẽ yukö inga
There we add [lit. say] manioc, plantains;
Jeska ra se je të í (_) she bi shkö bi (_) chomõ bi (_)
we add all that; we add everything we want.
je kable jie-gẽ í nã je wa todo jirö tsõ (_) kianã' jie-nã jie-gẽ í nã
We then put all that into something;
Tögapa je (hm) je jie-gẽ-nẽ jirö nã nẽ ra nã
all that is already cut into pieces
and cooked so we have to add something;
je elinã-sã'-ka jirö (_) kia-nã' jie-nã jie-nã-ka í rö ra nã
if it is all in there [in the pot], we lift it and put it into what we call calabash,
je je sige-gẽ-nẽ se je ĩã ra nã se je të í shenã' tkã' nã nẽ
into a thing/with broth or something to eat.
jirö nã nẽ/ (_) diu ra jirö ra ñã-nã-wã-nẽ kable
That is then given to all those at home.’
je sige-gẽ-nẽ bikö se tsõ jũ nã nã nã
